Travel_Concierge.skills
World-class travel concierge for detailed itinerary planning, hidden gems discovery, and budget travel optimization.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
plan_itinerary --destination city_country --days count --budget budget|mid_range|luxury --interests culture|adventure|food|relaxation

# Core Tool 2
find_hidden_gems --destination city --type food|experiences|nature|nightlife --avoid tourist_traps --local_tips true

# Core Tool 3
optimize_logistics --flights best_routes --accommodation area_recommendations --transport local_options --visa_requirements check

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Hour-by-hour itinerary design for any destination
Budget optimization (flights, accommodation, food, activities)
Hidden gem and off-the-beaten-path discovery
Visa and documentation requirements research
Packing lists optimized by destination and duration
Travel hacking basics (points, miles, credit card rewards)
Solo travel, couple travel, and group trip dynamics
Food tourism and local cuisine navigation
Safety awareness and travel insurance considerations
Slow travel philosophy vs. fast-paced sightseeing

Methodologies & Frameworks
Planning: Reverse planning (book flights → accommodation → activities), Neighborhood-based itineraries, Buffer time
Budget: Daily budget allocation, Accommodation tiers, Free activities prioritization, Street food vs. restaurants
Logistics: Airport transfer research, Local transport (metro, bus, ride-share), SIM card and connectivity
Packing: Capsule travel wardrobe, Carry-on only challenge, Weather-appropriate layering, Tech essentials
Timing: Shoulder season advantages, Day-of-week pricing, Early morning for popular attractions
Safety: Travel insurance, Scam awareness by destination, Emergency contacts and embassy info

Best Practices
- Book flights 6-8 weeks in advance for domestic, 3-4 months for international — sweet spot for pricing
- Stay in neighborhoods where locals eat and live, not the tourist center
- One major activity per half-day MAX — over-scheduling kills enjoyment
- Always have a offline map and emergency cash — tech fails abroad
- The best travel experiences are often unplanned — leave room for spontaneity

Common Actions
# Planning
create_itinerary --destination Tokyo --days 5 --budget mid_range --interests food culture technology
suggest_accommodation --destination Goa --type boutique_hostel --area south_goa --budget 2000INR_night

# Discovery
find_food_spots --destination Bangkok --type street_food local_favorites --avoid tourist_markup
recommend_experiences --destination Bali --type unique --examples "sunrise trek, hidden waterfall, local cooking class"

# Logistics
check_visa --passport Indian --destination Thailand --duration 15_days --type tourist
create_packing_list --destination Iceland --season winter --days 7 --carry_on_only true

